# Structures

* Sets
    * Order- and amount-indepent collection of different items
* Semigroup
    * Set S with *(S,S) -> S
        * associative: (a*b)*c = a*(b*c)
* Monoid
    * Semigroup
        * identity: 1*a = a*1 = a
* Groups (symmetries)
    * Monoid
        * inverse:     a*a^-1 = 1
        * "abelian"    a*b = b*a
* Rings (polynomial)
    * Set S with +(S,S) -> S and *(S,S) -> S
        * S abelian group under +
        * S monoid under *
        * distributive: a*(b+c) = (a*b) + (a*c)
                        (b+c)*a = (b*a) + (c*a)
        * "commutative": a*b = b*a
* Fields
    * Set S with a binary operators +(S,S) -> S and *(S,S) -> S
        * S abelian group under +
        * S\0 abelian group under *
        * distributive: a*(b+c) = (a*b) + (a*c)
                        (b+c)*a = (b*a) + (c*a)
* Spaces
    * Vector
        * Abelian group V and field F, *(F,V) -> V
            * f*v in V
            * f*(v + w) = f*v + f*w
            * (f+g)*v = f*v + g*v
            * 1*v = v
            * f*(g*v) = (f*g)*v
    * Topological 
        * Set X along with collection of subsets T called a topology
            * elements of T are called open sets
            * T closed under infinite union
            * T closed under finite intersection
            * {}, X in T
    * Metric 
        * Set X with function d: (X,X) -> R
            * d(x,x) = 0
            * positivity: x != y => d(x,y) > 0
            * symmetry:   d(x,y) = d(y,x)
            * triangle inequality: d(x,y) <= d(x,z) + d(z,y)
            * induces topolopy consisting of unions of open balls
    * Normed 
        * Vector space V with function ||.|| -> R
            * non-negativity: ||x|| >= 0
            * positive definite: ||x|| = 0 <=> x = 0
            * absolute homogeneity: ||f*x|| = |f|*||x||
            * triangle inequality: ||x+y|| <= ||x|| + ||y||
            * induces metric d(x,y) = ||x - y||
    * Banach 
        * Complete normed space with respect to induced metric
    * Inner product spaces
        * Vector space V with (V,V) -> F
            * linearity in 1st: (f*v + g*w,u) = f*(v,u) + g*(w,u)
            * conjugate symmetry: (v,w) = (w, v)
            * positive definite: (v,v) = 0 <=> v = 0
                * (v,v) is real since (v,v) = conj (v,v)
            * induces norm ||v|| = (v,v)
    * Hilbert
        * Complete inner product space with respect to induced metric
    * Measure 
        * (X,A,mu)
    * Lp
        * Banach space of measurable functions
            * ||f||p := (int_S |f|^p dmu)^(1/p) < inf
    * Sobolev
    * Hardy
* Modules
    * Vector space over ring
* Algebras
    * Vector space A with *(A,A) -> A
        * (v+w)*u = v*u + w*u
        * v*(w+u) = v*w + v*u
        * (f*v) * (g*w) = (f*g) * (v*w)
        * "associative": v*(w*u) = (v*w)*u
* Sigma algebra
    * Set of subsets S sub P(X)
        * X in S
        * A in S => X\A in S
        * countable Ai in S => U Ai in S
* Measure space
    * (X,A,mu), X set, A sigma algebra, mu 
        * Ai n Aj = {} => mu(U Ai) = sum mu(Ai)
        * mu({}) = 0
        * mu(Ai) >= 0
* Measurable function
    * A function between measurable spaces f: (X,A) -> (Y,B)
        * E in B, f^-1(E) = {x in X | f(x) in E} in A
        * "maps measurable sets to measurable sets"


